import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['delay'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: {data["delay"].mean():0.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():0.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Delay Time (minutes)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of delay time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['distance'])]
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axvline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?')
    ax.hist(data['distance'], bins=50, color='b')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Route')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?')
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['delay'], data['distance'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', label=f'Median Delay: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    ax.axhline(data['distance'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', label=f'Median Distance: {data["distance"].median():.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Delay Time')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distance Traveled')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by date?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
